Let $$a$$ and $$b$$ be [[Integers]] with [[Greatest Common Divisor]] $$d$$. Then, there exist integers $$x$$ and $$y$$ such that $$ax + by = d$$. More generally, the integers of the form $$ax + by$$ are exactly the multiples of $$d$$. 